Reasoning: The paper deals with analyzing the degrees of freedom (DoF) of a two-hop interference channel (IC) with linear schemes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of vector-linear strategies, which is a technique used in signal processing (cs.SI). The extension of the result to the multi-antenna setting involves the use of multiple antennas, which is a topic related to communication engineering (cs.CE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
